  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (software-fault gap probe)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD pipeline is implemented in a multi-threaded OpenFOAM-based solver with a Python orchestration layer that manages mesh partitioning, inter-process communication, and post-processing of the hemolysis power-law integral. All validation runs completed nominally; one isolated solver restart was logged but attributed to a cluster scheduler pre-emption and not investigated further. No fault-injection, NaN-propagation, or race-condition testing was performed on the solver or orchestration layer.",
